open_houses.description: FIRST WEEKEND | 226 Ritch #203 is a beautifully remodeled 1 bedroom, 1.5 bath loft WITH A/C in the center of exciting South Beach. A wall of windows bathes the open plan living and dining area in natural light and invites a look at the private outdoor space and city views; plus, hardwood floors throughout the lower level. The custom full bath is tastefully adorned in marble floor and wall tiles, accented with real wood cabinetry and doors, and finished off with stylish modern fixtures. Upstairs, the plush carpeted lofted bedroom boasts ample closet space and a convenient and stylish half bath. The updated chef's kitchen with stainless appliances, granite counters, and contemporary cabinetry rounds out this tastefully modern home. One car parking and storage, along with easy access to Caltrain, Muni, I280, and I80/Bay Bridge. With premier location to restaurants, cultural amenities, parks, transportation, shopping, Ritch #203 is the epitome of San Francisco urban living.

401 Dellbrook Avenue is a stylish urban oasis. Remodeled, bright, mid-century modern residence, desirable privacy, forest-view setting. Inviting formal entry leads to a grand living room, wood burning fireplace and calming views. Living room flows to expansive windows and area suitable for play & social gatherings. Solid oak floors, large master bedroom with large closet and attached master bathroom, second and third bedrooms and a second bathroom. Substantial kitchen, breakfast area, formal dining room and private patio area. Large garage + laundry area, bike & luggage storage plus large expansion potential. Fully detached, ample street parking. Clarendon Elementary School, children's playground, dog walking area, and a well-developed trail system + spectacular views. Golden Gate Park, 9th& Irving, West Portal, Castro, Cole Valley 10-minute jaunts. 401 Dellbrook Avenue is located in Midtown Terrace a quiet, calm, planned community & optimal home base for your San Francisco lifestyle
